Tetsu: MWUHAHAHAHAHA! Err....sorry for the sudden outburst and for not posting for awhile. Since Erin got her computer to work with DivX we've been living in her small room ^^;; watching anime with Indie & Erin..... -_- when they actually let us be alone in Indie's apartment she wouldn't let us use the computer -_-;; well anyway.... Indie says that she'll update the site with the holiday photos soon...and she will take more photos later too. Well I'll let Frayne write a bit before I need to use the computer to check my mail... Frayne: Hello everyone. Nice of you to read this, we've been pretty busy with watching japanese animated cartoons with Indego-san and Erin-san so we haven't had time to write here, I'm sorry. Pretty much has happened since the last time I wrote, Tetsu and I have celebrated the christian holiday, christmas, with Indego-san and her family. Then Indego-san, Erin-chan and I went to watch "Shark Tale" Tetsu, was supposed to come too but he changed his mind a couple of hours before and stayed home to watch "Murder she wrote -The movie " on tv, he was nice enough to tape it for Indego-san and Erin-san so we watched it everyone together the day after. Then we celebrated new year and last week Indego-san was home from work because she was sick and Erin-chan had a winter break from school so we have been cooped up in Erin-san's room. ^__^ I have also been posing for Indego-san for her new manga, I'm actually in it since it centers around a part of my life with some really important people to me....^____^ and Indego-san have said that some of them might even move in with us if we're lucky!!!.... heh, Tetsu is glaring at me. He doesn't want anymore people to move in, and I understand him but it would be really great if the whole old gang could get together again *sigh* I'm sorry but Tetsu is getting very impatiant, he wants to use the computer, so I guess I'll write more later. See you! First pic of the year!
http://mycolors.livejournal.com/2351.html

Tetsu: Oi, December definentily hasn't been a good month for poor Indego... I almost feel sorry for her....first off on the day Frayne arrived (O_o) her granddad (dad's dad) died.....then today her grandma (dad's ma) had to put down Tuffe (her grandma's beloved cat) because he had been hit by a car the night between sunday and monday.....and just about 3 hours ago she heard that her grandma (mom's mom) has gotten breast cancer (but don't tell anyone I told you, Indego wasn't supposed to tell anyone but she told me ^^;; )....so far as I know only Indego, her mom and I know about it.... Ah well....I need to go and help Frayne comfort Indego...the poor elf-boy don't have a clue to what's going on *sigh* ....-_-*...how troublesome.....
http://mycolors.livejournal.com/2200.html

Tetsu: Ah, hello there, haven't been online much these last couple of days. Indego & Erin-chan has been glued to the screen watching that FullMetal Alchemist anime like dogs in heat ^^;; They are really obsessing over that anime, luckily Gerd-san gave us movie tickets so the four of us could get out of the house. By the four of us I mean Indego, Erin-chan, Frayne and myself. The movie was hilarious and I'd recomend it....well anyway, I've got things to do I'll write more some other time.. ta dah! Frayne: Hello everyone, It's around 4 am and Indego-san & Erin-san is just about to go to bed, We have been to the theater to watch a move and then when we got back we watched some odd anime that Indego-san & Erin-san love. I don't think that it was a good movie for Erin-san to be watching, she is only 13 and the movie contained a lot a bad words and many references to sex. Oh, but I'm getting a head of myself, I haven't told you what movie we watched. It was named 'Bad Santa' and that the movie played as late as 9:30 pm should have given me an incling to what kind of movie it was. But I never thought that Indego-san would take us to a movie like that. But I have to admit that it wasn't so bad that I regret seeing it, and it was nice to get out a bit ^_^ Well, sadly, I can't write any more now because Tetsu wants to use to computer to write a bit on his book. Tetsu: Geez....What a couple of crazy days...first of Indego has finally gotten her fat ass out of the wagon and has updated the site. And I've gotten a new hair color....my hair is now brown... I like it better then my other hairdo. Mmm Indego has also had doubts about letting Jubei move in, but sadly she decided that she wanted him to come. We also have a new flatmate now, (I'm at least happy that it isn't jubei.) his name is Frayne and he is an elf. He's okay, he keeps to himself and also likes books so I guess I don't mind that he has moved in.... Frayne: Umm, Hello everyone! I have just moved in with Indie-san, Tet-san, PJ & Jack and I must say that I like it here so far. Jack & PJ are really great and Indie-san is really nice. Tet-san is the one I've spent the most time with so far since Indie-san is at work pretty often and PJ & Jack is out much. But I can't say that I know him so well. I don't think he likes to talk. -_- But what he do like to talk about is the guy who is going to move in here after New Year. I don't see what Tet-san finds so frusterating and annoying about Jubei-san, What I've heard about him makes him sound intriguing. I'm looking forward to meeting him after the new year has started. Geeze...I think Indego has finally lost it. Last night she woke me up and blabberd something about an elf moving in...yeah right, like an elf would want to movie in to this pigsty..... Well anyway, when Indego got home from work today we went right to Grandma Lodie and congratulated her on her birthday ^_^ we got chocolate cake...yummy!...and then 4 of her friends came -_- one of them said to me "Oh what a gorgeous girl" -_-;; When we said that I wasin't a girl, she became embarrased...I actually kind of liked her, that lady was spunky....then when we where about to leave, Indego's mom and little sister arrived...so we had to stay longer, just to supervise....but Indego's mom wasin't "in the fog" like Indego's Dad put's it...so it all went smoothly, I was down stairs with the old 'folks listening to them, while Indego and her little sister went up stairs to play.... When we finally was on our way home we went to a mini market and bought some food for PJ, Jack,Totte & Tuffe (T&T is Grandma Aina's cats)....I wanted to stay in the car...but NOOOOO...-_- Indego dragged me inside....luckily she was to lazy to take any photo's today...soo....ano, okay I need to go...indego want's to use the computer before she needs to go to bed......ta-tah!
